# Audit Instrumentation

Security-sensitive actions must call `logAudit` (or use store actions that already log internally).

## Already wired in store

`login`, `customer_reassigned`, `agent_created`, `agent_role_changed`, `agent_deleted`, `manual_share_created`, `manual_share_revoked`, `export_requested`, `export_approved`, `export_denied`, `data_exported`, `settings_changed` (field rules)

## Must wire when adding/touching these flows

| User action | `AuditAction` | Where |
|-------------|---------------|-------|
| Open customer detail (supervisor+) sees full phone | `phone_viewed_full` | `customers.tsx` — already on detail open |
| Customer create/edit/delete | `customer_created` / `customer_edited` / `customer_deleted` | store or route |
| Chat transfer | `conversation_transferred` | `ChatPage.tsx` — **currently missing** |
| Message delete | `conversation_deleted_message` | chat if feature exists |
| Template/tag/service CRUD | `settings_changed` | `settings.tsx` sections — **partially missing** |
| Agent online toggle | `agent_deactivated` | if treating offline as audit-worthy |

## Rules

- New `AuditAction` → add to `src/types/index.ts` union first
- Include `targetType`, `targetId`, `targetLabel`; use `oldValue`/`newValue` for diffs
- Label in audit UI uses Indonesian mapping in `settings.tsx` — add new action labels there
- Supervisor viewing audit: respect `canViewAuditEntry` — owner-only actions hidden

## Do not

- Log every button click — only security/governance events
- Log CS viewing masked phone (no full number exposed)
